Accepted theories state that investors require higher returns on riskier investments . 
I believe the risk for each individual stock selected by your pros is very large . 
Your hypothetical investor is simply being compensated for taking on this added risk . 
A four-stock portfolio is still exposed to a great deal of unnecessary risk . 
This means the returns can vary a great deal . 
Mr. Dorfman provides confirming evidence of this phenomenon when he reports that your staff of dart throwers would have accumulated only $ 112,383 by randomly selecting four new stocks to be held in a portfolio each month . 
The fact that stock pickers have bested a randomly selected portfolio in eight of 12 months has no bearing on the efficient-market theory . 
